						               													<description>&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#226;&amp;#150;&amp;#160;Idea of the Game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players play Hunter cards (Grim Reaper, Angel, and Devil cards) to fight over Soul cards.&amp;#10;Players fight over Soul cards on the table by playing Hunter cards from their hand. The player who has collected Soul cards of all 3 types, 3 Soul cards of the same type, or 5 Soul cards of any type wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#226;&amp;#150;&amp;#160;How to play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play a Hunter card from your hand face down on the Angel or Devil team side.&amp;#10;After all players pass their turns or the maximum number of Hunter cards playable (as shown on the Soul card) are played, flip all played Hunter cards face up. &amp;#10;Add the strength of the cards on each team side (Angel and Devil) to calculate the total strength of each team.&amp;#10;The player who played the Hunter card with the lowest number in the team with higher strength shall receive the Soul card of that round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#226;&amp;#150;&amp;#160;Point&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game, you need to play a high-number card(s) to form a majority and a low-number card(s) to outdo other players in the majority.&amp;#10;The point of this game lies on how you handle this dilemma.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
